- LCM approach: check divisibility by lcm of divisors to decide a combined token when using precedence pattern; for default rules lcm(3,5)=15.
- Digit-rule exactness: for digit_rules, define whether digit-based match should be combined with divisibility (e.g., contains digit 3 but not divisible by 3 still produces fizz) and whether digit-based tokens are appended or replace divisibility tokens.
- Error handling: validate that rules map does not contain zero as a divisor; throw IllegalArgumentException/ValueError/TypeError based on language.

